Words can not express how honored I am to be recognized by a company I truly believe in. Thank you @f45_training for this award. This was an absolute team effort. So I’d really like to show some appreciation to my people ❤️

To my business partners thank you for always pushing me to reach new heights and never letting me fall.

To our staff thank you for showcasing your love for fitness, and our members each day. Y’all are the true hero’s 🔥🔥 I am so proud of each and every one of you! 

To the community thank you for believing in us so we can continue to believe in you each day. From the amazing transformations to the day to day grind. You ALL are the reason we love what we do. 

I am so honored and blessed to be a part of this movement. Being able to say you love what you do is one thing. But to be able to build something incredible, with people who share the same passion is when you know you’re in the right place. #sanantonio let’s show the world what we are made of 🔥🔥

My favorite ways to enhance my endurance 🫀🧠

Kickboxing: POWER+SPEED+COORDINATION
I have been training with the one and only @echolsfitnesscenter Learning a new sport brings back my competitive nature. And its really testing my athletic ability physically and mentally. Getting one on one training to bring awareness to the fine details to help perfect the techniques. It’s been a blast!! 

Animal flow: MOBILITY+BALANCE+FLEXIBILITY 
I am falling in love with this new style of training. Getting lost in movement and balance. Never have I put my body through such a graceful way of training. And I like how creative it allows me to be when I am putting my own combinations together. Just throw on my music and vibe 🙏🏼 The physical and mental benefits give me similar relief as mediation, breathing, and stretching would. 

F45 Functional training: STRENGTH+FUNCTIONALITY+METABOLIC TRAINING 
My first love ❤️ F45 provide the variety of workouts and movements that my body needs. I am able to test a lot of what I incorporate into my training routines into these classes. It’s essentially like a benchmark of training. And I love the vibes. Always motivating and fun. 
 #sport #mobility #functional

Let’s chat 🙏🏼 
Life has taken some insane turns. And all is in the grace of evolving as a human and knowing where my heart is guiding me. Trust me there is nothing better then a solid support system. But when you completely immerse yourself in something new you have to really only count in yourself. Change is scary y’all 😅 Its times like these that challenge you to show yourself what you are truly made of. Love yourself to a point that giving up on you will never be an option ✊🏽Recreating should be fun and exciting. Enjoy each moment of falling in love with your new beginning. Because that is the part of the journey you will respect the most ✊🏽 #letsgrow

Progress is exciting!!! I’m not gonna to pretend like I didn’t eat and drink whatever I wanted on my bday. Nor will I pretend that I have the same 21 year old bender bounce back capabilities🥴🥴. But what I can say is I’m loving this new freedom I’ve been having with my diet, and workouts lately. So throwing in new things just experiment has been cool. 
Mind you I have been training consistently since I was in high school sports. I just have been evolving into new habits, new techniques, and new routines. I stick to what works for ME and I progress accordingly. Il say that I do have more on then off days. But I honestly found joy in making myself better and learning more. The process is the most interesting part. It’s unique to everyone and it’s something that is constantly being developed. I love mine in every shape size and and direction it presented itself. #thatsme

Been wearing confidence a lot lately 🙏🏼✨

I haven’t touched a football, let alone a field in years.Ive been honestly very intimidated to play or run full speed since my ACL surgery. 
I let loose today ran routes, trained like I used to, and ran full speed multiple times 🔥🔥 and it felt good!! 
It’s crazy how after 4 years my body is not only familiar to this training but it has improved! Back when I was playing sports I was reckless aggressive and only trained to be stronger and faster. Mobility, nutrition, and recover were not a high priority to me. If only I knew then what I know know now. I haven’t had this exhausted fun feeling in awhile. It’s nice to know that even through that era ended years ago it still brings me the same joy it used to. Btw…. We still got it 😏 

#forevertomboy #athlete

social_posts.post_text: Turning it up to 10 😈🔥 excited for this new chapter. Starting something new is challenging. It will never get easier you just get better at building. One week of opening my own platform…I’ve met so many incredible people with incredible stories. Im In a new space that allows me to scale the innovation in my training style. And I’m looking and feeling better then I ever have. Life is good and we are feeding into this new 🔥 energy.

I’m free, but I’m focused 🕊️

June thank you for all the incredible things you taught me! Month one of our #M3thodtraining launch was absolutely incredible. Meeting so many amazing people, and kick starting so many new journeys. Needless to say I am proud of the team and new clients who are taking these next steps. July, is going to be a fun month. #letskeepgrowing🌱

Imagine if you went all in? You put in that 110%. You did ALL of the work and then some. You DIDNT give up. And you pushed all the way to the end. Do you think you would be better for it? Would you consider yourself a winner in the end? 
This type of mindset  is absolutely not easy. It will take time and efforts to really see progress. In the end you will prove one of two things to yourself. You are not willing, or your are capable to achieve. 

Todays workout was brutal. Training for my first @hyroxworld competition has been insanely humbling to say the least. 
Big shout out to my coach @builtbywill for exposing my weakness. But hey now we know where need need to improve. 
I am a trainer yes, but this is a whole new way of training that I am unfamiliar with. It’s been fun to learn and challenge my body and level of discipline. Having a coach that can guide you, hold you accountable, and teach you will take you to that next level. 

This chapter of my life is called: “RESILIENCE”
